• Added a button to access the Application development policy and EULA in the application info interface (due to ADP update);
• Added automatic check for updates to the application info interface

Version 2.13h:
• Input and output paths will be saved on exit and restored on startup of application;
• New application info interface implemented

Version 2.12.5L:
• Applied correct representation of supported languages list;
• Fixed reactivation of palettes button after first conversion when it must be blocked due to absence of codecs library

Version 2.12.2:
• Application icon updated;
• Minor interface bugs fixed

Version 2.12:
• Added compatibility control for codecs library;
• User interface has been reviewed using tab control

Version 2.11u:
• Application namespace, icon and development environment have been unified;
• Localization system unified;
• Progress bar has been updated;
• ASE palette processing bug fixed;
• Some interface improvements applied

Version 2.10:
• Max linear size of pictures increased up to 2^14;
• Some interface bugs fixed;
• “Include subfolders” flag added; it allows scanning all files in all tree of directories

Version 2.9:
• Bad memory management fixed: it will be used properly since this version;
• Some interface improvements applied

Version 2.8.1:
• Inability to opening PCX files with monochrome palettes fixed

Version 2.8:
• Support of JPEG2000 removed due to instability of OpenJPEG library;
• Added English language support for main interface;
• Free input of source and target paths allowed

Version 2.7:
• Image cropping added. For now it is an area in the center of image. Its width and height may be specified manually. Moving of area will be implemented later;
• B&W PBM format processing bugs fixed;
• JPEG2000 format writing disabled due to unpredictable crushes; we work on it now

Version 2.6:
• JPEG2000 files with no color space specified now open properly;
• JPEG2000 .jpt format support removed (because OpenJPEG has no real support for it);
• Set of JPEG2000 file extensions expanded;
• JPEG2000 alpha channel support added (for reading; writing doesn’t work properly);
• JPEG2000 format writing added;
• “Alpha-channel to bitmap mode” conversion bug fixed;
• Other alpha-channel processing bugs fixed

Version 2.5:
• Some palettes manager’s interface improvements applied;
• Some image processing bugs fixed;
• Color table’s visualization bug fixed;
• ACO and ASE palettes formats support added;
• Brightness edge for bitmap conversion now can be specified

Version 2.4:
• Some class structure optimizations performed;
• Palettes manager added:
  • Supports Adobe Color Tables (.act), Microsoft Palette and JASC palette (.pal) reading and writing;
  • Supports Windows bitmap (.bmp) and ZSoft paintbrush (.pcx) palettes extracting;
  • Supports creation, editing, loading and saving operations;
  • Supports alpha-channel setting;
  • Supports Windows bitmap image palette replacing.
• Some interface improvements performed

Version 2.3:
• JPEG2000 format added. Used OpenJPEG default codec;
• Max linear image size increased to 8192 px (special for smartphone’s photos with 3120 x 4160 quality);
• Fatal library linking defect fixed. Now it can be really used on another PC’s;
• .tif and .tiff, .jpe and .jpeg extensions double processing fixed;
• PCX format parser memory leak fixed;
• Images processing interface have been improved

Version 2.2:
• Added “relative image size change” option;
• Some core improvements added

Version 2.1:
• Added library of external format codecs;
• Added TGA and PCX formats support (read/write). Thanks for materials from Codenet and Xash3D project

Version 2.0:
• Application’s core has been upgraded for adding new file formats and effects support;
• “Portable bitmaps” (PBM/PGM/PPM/PNM) reading and writing support added;
• “Windows metafiles” (WMF/EMF) and “Windows icons” formats reading support added

Version 1.3:
• Maximum image dimension (width and height) increased to 4096 px;
• Some interface artifacts fixed;
• Image mode (color/greyscale/bitmap) selection added; greyscale conversion uses HDTV coefficients;
• Image flip and rotation added;
• Alpha-channel now supported in all available directions

Version 1.2:
• Publication on GitHub
